<dl id="n12215d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12215d">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12215d"> 215(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Kevin&apos;s remembered / whipping</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">On s&apos;&eacute;tonne que les peuples prennent plaisir &agrave; comm&eacute;morer leurs d&eacute;faites. La douleur r&eacute;trospective qu&apos;ils y &eacute;prouvent est une source d&apos;intimes satisfactions. Le go&ucirc;t esth&eacute;tique de la douleur n&apos;est pas une d&eacute;pravation sentimentale de l&apos;humanit&eacute; vieillie, ni un raffinement de son &acirc;ge adulte. <br><font color="green">[One is surprised that people enjoy commemorating their defeats. Retrospective pain is the source of intimate satisfactions. The esthetic taste of pain is neither the sentimental depravity of an aged humanity nor the refinement of an adult age]</font> <small> Stefan Czarnowski, <a name="SCSP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SCSP"><cite title="source">Le culte des h&eacute;ros et ses conditions sociale: saint Patrick, h&eacute;ros nationale de l'Irlande</cite></a> (1919) LXXXVI</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
